# Crypto and provider tickers (CHILI)

## App convention (DB, UI, backtests, yfinance-style)

- Use **`BASE-USD`** (hyphen), e.g. `ZK-USD`, `BTC-USD`.
- **Bare concat** is also valid crypto input: **`ZKUSD`**, **`BTCUSD`** (no hyphen, ends with `USD`, base 2–15 alnum). Treat as crypto everywhere you branch on asset class.

## Massive / Polygon REST (aggregates, snapshots)

- Provider symbols are **`X:BASEQUOTE`** (no hyphen in the pair), e.g. `X:ZKUSD`, `X:BTCUSD`.
- **Do not** assume `X:BASEUSD` is the only listing. The same asset may trade as **`X:BASEUSDT`** or **`X:BASEUSDC`**.

## Single source of truth (implement here, do not fork logic)

| Function | Module | Role |
|----------|--------|------|
| `to_massive_ticker` | `app/services/massive_client.py` | `ZK-USD` / `ZKUSD` → `X:ZKUSD`; stocks pass through |
| `crypto_aggregate_symbol_candidates` | same | Ordered list: primary + `USD` / `USDT` / `USDC` variants |
| `massive_aggregate_variants_all_dead` | same | True only if **every** candidate is in the dead cache (avoid skipping Massive when one quote pair is dead) |
| `is_crypto` | same | `*-USD`, bare `*USD`, not `X:` prefixes |
| `from_massive_ticker` | same | `X:…` → app `BASE-USD` (handles USDT/USDC suffixes) |

- **`get_aggregates`** in Massive and Polygon tries **`crypto_aggregate_symbol_candidates`** until bars are returned.
- **`polygon_client`** imports `is_crypto`, `to_massive_ticker`, and `crypto_aggregate_symbol_candidates` from **`massive_client`** (same package: `from .massive_client import …`). Keep naming aligned; do not duplicate variant lists in Polygon-only code.

## `market_data` and tests

- **`fetch_ohlcv` / `fetch_ohlcv_df`**: use **`massive_aggregate_variants_all_dead(ticker)`** (not only `to_massive_ticker`) when deciding if Massive is exhausted.
- When mocking **`_massive`** in tests, set **`massive_aggregate_variants_all_dead.return_value = False`** if the code path should fall through to Polygon/yfinance (otherwise a `MagicMock` is truthy and blocks fallbacks).

## Anti-patterns

- Treating a **404 or empty** on **`X:BASEUSD`** as “coin unavailable” without trying **USDT/USDC** candidates.
- Marking the **entire** asset dead because **one** intraday chunk or **one** quote currency failed (per-symbol / per-variant dead cache only).
- Hardcoding `X:…` strings in routers or templates instead of normalizing through **`to_massive_ticker`** / candidates.
